      "description": "Generic massive one-loop pentagon integral family with 5 propagators and generic internal and external masses, used as the maximal topology for $d_{int}=4$ one-loop integrals. Serves as the framework for constructing dual forms (elements of twisted relative cohomology) and computing generalized unitarity coefficients via intersection numbers. The paper shows a complete basis of 31 master integrals for generic masses (1 pentagon, 5 boxes, 10 triangles, 10 bubbles, 5 tadpoles).",
